addBefore

public void addBefore(com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.Widget widgetToAdd,
                      com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.Widget nextWidget)
Adds a widget to the token separated list before the specified widget. You should only add inline widgets (not block widget), such as Anchor, InlineLabel, InlineHyperlink or InlineHTML.

Parameters:
widgetToAdd - The widget to add.
nextWidget - The widget before which to add. Pass null to insert at the end.

setWidgetVisible

public void setWidgetVisible(com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.Widget widget,
                             boolean visible)
Call this to make a widget visible or invisible. You should not call setVisible() directly on the widget, otherwise its separating token will be lost.

Parameters:
widget - The widget on which to change visibility.
visible - The desired visibility.
